=Description=

Ethan Zuckerman, the director of the MIT Center for Civic Media, visited Google's Cambridge, MA office to discuss why the technological ability to communicate with someone does not inevitably lead to increased human connection.

:Ethan Zuckerman directs the Center for Civic Media at MIT, and teaches at MIT’s Media Lab. He’s the co-founder of global blogging community Global Voices, and he works with social change nonprofit organizations around the world. He’s an alumnus of the Berkman Center at Harvard, Geekcorps, and Tripod. 

